base.substitutions = c("AT.GC", "AT.CG", "AT.TA", "CG.TA", "CG.AT", "CG.GC")
possible.columns = paste("POSSIBLE.TOTAL", base.substitutions,  sep=".")
total.columns = paste("OBSERVED.TOTAL", base.substitutions,  sep=".")
base.sub = data.frame(type = as.factor(base.substitutions), possible = as.numeric(count[possible.columns]), total = as.numeric(count[total.columns]))
base.sub
##    type possible total
## 1 AT.GC  3033922     5
## 2 AT.CG  3033922     3
## 3 AT.TA  3033922    13
## 4 CG.TA  2225232    22
## 5 CG.AT  2225232     6
## 6 CG.GC  2225232     2
one.rate = glm(total ~ possible + 0, data=base.sub, family=poisson())
# Fit the six rate model, use glm()
six.rate = glm(total ~ possible + type + 0, data=base.sub, family=poisson())

# Perform a likelihood ratio test to compare the model fits
anova(one.rate, six.rate, test="LRT")

# Function to create heatmap matrix for a given protein dataframe
create_heatmap_dataframe <- function(df) {
  df %>%
    group_by(Residue, Strain) %>%
    summarize(Count = sum(Count), .groups = "drop") %>%  
    pivot_wider(names_from = Strain, values_from = Count, values_fill = 0) %>%
    as.data.frame() 
}


# Create heatmap matrices for each protein
heatmap_df1 <- create_heatmap_dataframe(CAP1_df)
heatmap_df2 <- create_heatmap_dataframe(CAP2_df)
heatmap_df3 <- create_heatmap_dataframe(CAP3_df)

heatmap_df1[,2:ncol(heatmap_df1)] <- heatmap_df1[,2:ncol(heatmap_df1)] - heatmap_df1$`3-2B`
heatmap_df2[,2:ncol(heatmap_df2)] <- heatmap_df2[,2:ncol(heatmap_df2)] - heatmap_df2$`3-2B`
heatmap_df3[,2:ncol(heatmap_df3)] <- heatmap_df3[,2:ncol(heatmap_df3)] - heatmap_df3$`3-2B`

convert_to_matrix <- function(df) {
  matrix_result <- as.matrix(df[, -1])
  rownames(matrix_result) <- df$Residue
  
  return(matrix_result)
}

heatmap_matrix1 <- convert_to_matrix(heatmap_df1)
heatmap_matrix2 <- convert_to_matrix(heatmap_df2)
heatmap_matrix3 <- convert_to_matrix(heatmap_df3)

# Extract annotations
row_anno <- msa_counts2 %>%
  select(Residue, ResidueType) %>%
  distinct() %>%
  arrange(match(Residue, rownames(heatmap_matrix1)))

col_anno <- msa_counts2 %>%
  select(Strain, StrainType) %>%
  distinct() %>%
  arrange(match(Strain, colnames(heatmap_matrix1)))

# Create row and column annotations
row_annotation <- rowAnnotation(
  ResidueType = row_anno$ResidueType,
  col = list(ResidueType = c("Polar" = "lightblue", "Nonpolar" = "orange", 
                             "Basic" = "purple", "Acidic" = "red")),show_annotation_name = FALSE
)

column_annotation <- columnAnnotation(
  StrainType = col_anno$StrainType,
  col = list(StrainType = c("Evolved" = "#1b9e77", "Parent" = "#fdbb84")),show_annotation_name = FALSE
)
col_fun <- colorRamp2(c(-2, 0, 2), c("blue", "grey", "red"))

# Apply to Heatmap
#CAP1
Heatmap(heatmap_matrix1,
        name = "Delta",
        column_title = "CAP1",
        cluster_rows = FALSE,
        cluster_columns = FALSE,
        show_row_names = TRUE,
        top_annotation = column_annotation,
        left_annotation = row_annotation,
        show_column_names = TRUE,
        row_names_side = "left",
        column_names_side = "bottom",
        col = col_fun
)

#CAP2
Heatmap(heatmap_matrix2,
        name = "Delta",
        column_title = "CAP2",
        cluster_rows = FALSE,
        cluster_columns = FALSE,
        show_row_names = TRUE,
        top_annotation = column_annotation,
        left_annotation = row_annotation,
        show_column_names = TRUE,
        row_names_side = "left",
        column_names_side = "bottom",
        col = col_fun
)

#CAP3
Heatmap(heatmap_matrix3,
        name = "Delta",
        column_title = "CAP3",
        cluster_rows = FALSE,
        cluster_columns = FALSE,
        show_row_names = TRUE,
        top_annotation = column_annotation,
        left_annotation = row_annotation,
        show_column_names = TRUE,
        row_names_side = "left",
        column_names_side = "bottom",
        col = col_fun
)
